    "summary": "During temporary abandonment operations on well A-26, an injured person attempted to close the Lower Manual Master Valve using a 36-inch aluminum pipe wrench due to trapped pressure. The wrench slipped off the valve wheel and struck the person in the mouth, breaking both top front teeth and causing a minor laceration to the lower lip.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Use a valve wrench for turning a valve wheel instead of an aluminum pipe wrench"
    ],
